        "type": "User",
        "site_admin": false,
        "name": null,
        "patch_url": null
      },
      "body": "Thx, done. Though, I left out the style stuff, because trailing multi-line comments are supported, they just look ugly. Also, some devs may not care about having to re-flow.\r\n\r\nFor reference, I also don't like `/** */`, because devs often forget the second star (`*`), turning it into a code comment, not a doxygen comment. Also, they are inconsistently used (even in the same class):\r\n\r\n```cpp\r\n/** one */\r\n\r\n/**\r\n * two */\r\n\r\n/** three_a\r\n * three_b\r\n */\r\n\r\n/**\r\n * four\r\n */\r\n```\r\n\r\nThough, at least they are not actively wrong, like the trailing comments, so I don't really mind too much.",
      "created_at": "2026-04-02T13:50:38Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-02T13:50:39Z",
